Package org.yawlfoundation.yawl.resourcing.rsInterface

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ConnectionCache
    An extended HashMap to handle connections from external entities (such as the YAWL Editor) and the resource service.
    ResourceCalendarGateway
    The Calendar Gateway class acts as an API gateway between the resource service and its calendar sub-service.
    ResourceCalendarGatewayClient  
    ResourceGateway
    The Resource Gateway class acts as a gateway between the Resource Service and the external world for resource (org data) maintenance.
    ResourceGatewayClient
    An API to be used by clients for retrieving organisational model data from the Resource Service.
    ResourceGatewayClientAdapter
    This adapter class adds a transformation layer to the resource gateway client, effectively reconstituting the Strings returned from the gateway into java objects.
    ResourceGatewayServer
    Author: Michael Adams Creation Date: 12/06/2009
    ResourceLogGateway
    The Log Gateway class acts as an API gateway between the resource service and its process logs.
    ResourceLogGatewayClient
    An API to be used by clients that want to retrieve data from the resource service process logs.
    ResourceMarshaller
    Author: Michael Adams Creation Date: 9/03/2008
    ServiceConnection
    Author: Michael Adams Date: Oct 24, 2007 Time: 1:06:45 PM
    ServiceConnectionTimer  
    UserConnection
    Author: Michael Adams Creation Date: 28/04/2010
    UserConnectionCache
    Author: Michael Adams Creation Date: 28/04/2010
    WorkQueueGateway
    The WorkQueue Gateway provides a gateway (or a set of API) between the Resource Service and the participant workqueue jsps.
    WorkQueueGatewayClient
    The WorkQueue Gateway externalises the full worklist functionality of the Resource Service by providign a gateway (or a set of API) between the Service and the participant workqueue jsps.
    WorkQueueGatewayClientAdapter
    This adapter class adds a transformation layer to the resource gateway client, effectively reconstituting the Strings returned from the gateway into java objects.
